FBIS4-9512 "dreeu082_c_94002" FBIS-EEU-94-082 Daily Report 25 Apr 1994 CZECH REPUBLIC Dukovany Plant Considered `Safe and Reliable' Dukovany Plant Considered `Safe and Reliable' AU2604161794 Prague MLADA FRONTA DNES in Czech 25 Apr 94 p 3 AU2604161794 Prague MLADA FRONTA DNES Czech BFN [Article by "(dz)": "There Were More Than 300 Cases of Malfunction at Dukovany in 1993"] [Text] Dukovany--At the Dukovany nuclear plant, in the vicinity of which environmentalists commemorated the eighth anniversary of the Chernobyl disaster, there were 315 cases of malfunction and deviations from the standard. Three of them were described as failures due to flaws in security measures. The report that the State Office for Nuclear Safety drafted for the government states that the emergency signaling systems were activated 12 times in 1993. Despite this, the State Office for Nuclear Safety considers the operation of the Dukovany nuclear plant to be safe and reliable.
